    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.add​(int, V)
    order isn't guaranteed, so index parameter does nothing
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.addAll​(int, Collection<? extends V>)
    order isn't guaranteed, so index parameter does nothing. use AbstractCollection.addAll(java.util.Collection) instead.
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.first()
    order isn't guaranteed, may return different values per call.
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.get​(int)
    this implementation always throws exception since it does not have order
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.indexOf​(Object)
    this implementation always throws exception since it does not have order
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.last()
    order isn't guaranteed, may return different values per call.
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.lastIndexOf​(Object)
    this implementation always throws exception since it does not have order
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.remove​(int)
    this implementation always throws exception since it does not have order
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.reverse()
    order isn't guaranteed, so this call does nothing.
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.set​(int, V)
    this implementation always throws exception since it does not have order
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.shift()
    this implementation always throws exception since it does not have order (we can't determine what element/index to shift)
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.shuffle()
    order isn't guaranteed, so this call does nothing.
    xyz.mlserver.javautil.CollectionSet.unshift​(V...)
    this implementation always throws exception since it does not have order
